        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I suppose that makes sense for broad integration coverage but I think we agree that the current way that we fail is not ideal b/c the test collapses the the way that the curl fails \ninto just `post.method == nil`.\n\nI now suggest a minimum set of fixds as:\n\n1. fix the `t.eq()` argument order\n2. assert & print `post.error` / decoded response _before_ checking fields, so we can see why the failure occurs\n3. add a retry around the actual request/assertion live because HTTP failures are part of the network integration contract (<- the only thing to actually de-flake the test)\n\n",
            "created_at": "2026-05-03T16:05:01Z",
